{"tags": ["books", "library"], "text": "\u201cI have always imagined that Paradise will be a kind of library.\u201d", "author": "Jorge Luis Borges"}
{"tags": ["books", "inspirational", "reading", "tea"], "text": "\u201cYou can never get a cup of tea large enough or a book long enough to suit me.\u201d", "author": "C.S. Lewis"}
{"tags": ["books", "thought"], "text": "\u201cIf you only read the books that everyone else is reading, you can only think what everyone else is thinking.\u201d", "author": "Haruki Murakami"}
{"tags": ["books", "friends", "novelist-quotes"], "text": "\u201cThere is no friend as loyal as a book.\u201d", "author": "Ernest Hemingway"}
{"tags": ["authors", "books", "literature", "reading", "writing"], "text": "\u201cWhat really knocks me out is a book that, when you're all done reading it, you wish the author that wrote it was a terrific friend of yours and you could call him up on the phone whenever you felt like it. That doesn't happen much, though.\u201d", "author": "J.D. Salinger"}
{"tags": ["books", "classic", "reading"], "text": "\u201c\u2032Classic\u2032 - a book which people praise and don't read.\u201d", "author": "Mark Twain"}
{"tags": ["books", "library", "reading"], "text": "\u201cI declare after all there is no enjoyment like reading! How much sooner one tires of any thing than of a book! -- When I have a house of my own, I shall be miserable if I have not an excellent library.\u201d", "author": "Jane Austen"}
{"tags": ["books", "children", "difficult", "grown-ups", "write", "writers", "writing"], "text": "\u201cYou have to write the book that wants to be written. And if the book will be too difficult for grown-ups, then you write it for children.\u201d", "author": "Madeleine L'Engle"}
{"tags": ["inspirational", "life", "live", "miracle", "miracles"], "text": "\u201cThere are only two ways to live your life. One is as though nothing is a miracle. The other is as though everything is a miracle.\u201d", "author": "Albert Einstein"}
