{"text": "\u201cI declare after all there is no enjoyment like reading! How much sooner one tires of any thing than of a book! -- When I have a house of my own, I shall be miserable if I have not an excellent library.\u201d", "tags": ["books", "library", "reading"], "author": "Jane Austen"}
{"text": "\u201cYou have to write the book that wants to be written. And if the book will be too difficult for grown-ups, then you write it for children.\u201d", "tags": ["books", "children", "difficult", "grown-ups", "write", "writers", "writing"], "author": "Madeleine L'Engle"}
